                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d739">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/10–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sands</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-06T13:00:00+03:06"
                            >October 6, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>375. ReLegtel 374 October 5. King also wishes to publish at same time his letter
                    of March 10 to President Roosevelt<note n="60" xml:id="d739fn60">Not printed,
                        but see footnote 39, <ref target="#pg_692">p. 692</ref>.</note> to which
                    latter’s [letter?] of April was in answer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sands</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
